Hi

I've found no way to search for any specific type of subtask. 
*Background:*
We are running a Changes Management system through JIRA, and using a set of customized workflows and issue types. And we need to have a set of custom reports on top of it. Among these reports we need to have a report that will give "all issues of type A, that have subissues of type B". 

*Idea*
Ideally it could work if we will be able to run something like
{code}
issue HAS subIssuesIn("subquery for subissues"). 
{code}
This will allow to look for any subissues we need and will grant us great flexibility. 

Optionally, with less flexibility it would work with a function like
{code}
issue HAS subIssuesType("subissue type B"). 
{code}
This will have much less flexibility, but will allow to solve current problem.

Thanks.

